text: Villafranca is a habitational surname of Spanish and Italian origin. ==Notable people== Notable people with this surname include: * Fernando Villafranca (born 1993), Mexican boxer * Juan de Villafranca (born 1954), Mexican diplomat * Vincent Villafranca (born 1969), American sculptor ==See also== * Villafranca (disambiguation)
